Duduzane Zuma has raised questions over why he was not provided a fair opportunity by former Public Protector Thuli Madonsela to give his version of events – in the manner in which Former Deputy Finance Minister Mcebisi Jonas did. Former president Jacob Zuma’s son is testifying at the Commission of Inquiry into State Capture in Parktown, Johannesburg. Jonas has previously testified that Duduzane introduced him to the controversial Gupta family at their Saxonworld home in 2015. He claimed that one of the Gupta brothers offered him the position of Finance Minister for R600-million. Zuma has raised concerns over why he was not requested to provide his statement to the then Public Protector. Click link for more on the story:     